        "created_at": "2022-08-08T22:11:02.284Z",
        "cooked": "<p>Apologies if this has already been discussed, but I saw this come across HN last week and thought you all would find it really interesting. It appears to be fairly new, but looks to be a really promising layer addition.</p>\n<p><strong>Features</strong></p>\n<ul>\n<li>\n<strong>Full feature-set from SQLite</strong>: mvsqlite integrates with SQLite using a custom <a href=\"https://www.sqlite.org/vfs.html\" rel=\"noopener nofollow ugc\">VFS</a> layer.</li>\n<li>\n<strong>Time travel</strong>: Checkout the snapshot of your database at any point of time in the past.</li>\n<li>\n<strong>Zero-overhead multi-database transactions</strong>: While each SQLite database remains single-writer, you can horizontally scale your application with multi-database strictly serializable transactions without additional overhead. <a href=\"https://github.com/losfair/mvsqlite/wiki/Commit-group\" rel=\"noopener nofollow ugc\">How to use</a>\n</li>\n<li>\n<strong>Get the nice properties from FoundationDB, without its limits</strong>: <a href=\"https://apple.github.io/foundationdb/testing.html\" rel=\"noopener nofollow ugc\">Correctness</a>, <a href=\"https://apple.github.io/foundationdb/performance.html\" rel=\"noopener nofollow ugc\">really fast and scalable</a> distributed transactions, synchronous and asynchronous replication, integrated backup and restore. Meanwhile, there\u2019s no <a href=\"https://apple.github.io/foundationdb/known-limitations.html\" rel=\"noopener nofollow ugc\">five-second transaction limit</a> any more, and a SQLite transaction can be ~39x larger than FDB\u2019s native transaction.</li>\n<li>\n<strong>Drop-in replacement</strong>: Set the <code>LD_PRELOAD=libmvsqlite_preload.so</code> environment variable and your existing apps will work out of the box.</li>\n</ul>\n<aside class=\"onebox allowlistedgeneric\" data-onebox-src=\"https://github.com/losfair/mvsqlite\">\n  <header class=\"source\">\n      <img src=\"https://github.githubassets.com/favicons/favicon.svg\" class=\"site-icon\" width=\"32\" height=\"32\">\n\n      <a href=\"https://github.com/losfair/mvsqlite\" target=\"_blank\" rel=\"noopener nofollow ugc\">GitHub</a>\n  </header>\n\n  <article class=\"onebox-body\">\n    <div class=\"aspect-image\" style=\"--aspect-ratio:690/345;\"><img src=\"https://global.discourse-cdn.com/foundationdb/optimized/2X/e/ee90f21db8b51c55ea0040115ebf5bbfdacc0179_2_690x345.png\" class=\"thumbnail\" width=\"690\" height=\"345\" srcset=\"https://global.discourse-cdn.com/foundationdb/optimized/2X/e/ee90f21db8b51c55ea0040115ebf5bbfdacc0179_2_690x345.png, https://global.discourse-cdn.com/foundationdb/optimized/2X/e/ee90f21db8b51c55ea0040115ebf5bbfdacc0179_2_1035x517.png 1.5x, https://global.discourse-cdn.com/foundationdb/original/2X/e/ee90f21db8b51c55ea0040115ebf5bbfdacc0179.png 2x\" data-small-upload=\"https://global.discourse-cdn.com/foundationdb/optimized/2X/e/ee90f21db8b51c55ea0040115ebf5bbfdacc0179_2_10x10.png\"></div>\n\n<h3><a href=\"https://github.com/losfair/mvsqlite\" target=\"_blank\" rel=\"noopener nofollow ugc\">GitHub - losfair/mvsqlite: Distributed, MVCC SQLite that runs on FoundationDB.</a></h3>\n\n  <p>Distributed, MVCC SQLite that runs on FoundationDB. - GitHub - losfair/mvsqlite: Distributed, MVCC SQLite that runs on FoundationDB.</p>\n\n\n  </article>\n\n  <div class=\"onebox-metadata\">\n    \n    \n  </div>\n\n  <div style=\"clear: both\"></div>\n</aside>\n",
